| `src/services/service_manager.cpp/h` | Pool creation and management |
| `src/processing/stream_processor.cpp/h` | Arena injection |
| `src/processing/etl_pipeline.cpp` | Arena injection |
| `src/processing/batch_processor.cpp` | Arena injection |
| `src/services/scheduling_service.cpp` | Arena injection |

### 5.4 Expected Outcome
With this solution implemented:
- Real-time alerting latency will remain **stable** regardless of batch workload
- Batch jobs will use remaining CPU capacity without impacting SLAs
- The solution is **minimally invasive**, extending rather than replacing existing patterns
- Configuration is **tunable** for different deployment scenarios

